I will now implement the required database triggers, Row-Level Security (RLS) policies, and the API middleware for setting the tenant context.

First, I will create a new SQL migration file to define the `edges_validate` trigger and enable RLS for all tenant-scoped tables. This ensures data integrity for relationships and strict data isolation between tenants at the database level.

Next, I will create a new Fastify plugin. This plugin will act as middleware, running before every request. It will extract a tenant ID from the `x-tenant-id` header, validate it, and then set a session-level configuration variable (`app.tenant_id`) in PostgreSQL. This variable is crucial for the RLS policies to work correctly, as they will filter data based on its value.

Finally, I will register this new plugin in the main API server file, ensuring it loads after the database connection is established but before any routes are processed. This guarantees that the tenant context is set for every database query made during a request.

